{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":724,"text":"This is poo,"},{"time":2972,"text":"and what I want to do today is share my passion"},{"time":5455,"text":"for poo with you,"},{"time":8598,"text":"which might be quite difficult,"},{"time":11411,"text":"but I think what you might find more fascinating"},{"time":14504,"text":"is the way these small animals deal with poo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17705,"text":"So this animal here has got a brain"},{"time":20057,"text":"about the size of a grain of rice, and yet it can do things"},{"time":24017,"text":"that you and I couldn't possibly entertain the idea of doing."},{"time":27767,"text":"And basically it's all evolved to handle its food source,"},{"time":31889,"text":"which is dung."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34023,"text":"So the question is, where do we start this story?"},{"time":36602,"text":"And it seems appropriate to start at the end,"},{"time":39627,"text":"because this is a waste product that comes out"},{"time":42412,"text":"of other animals, but it still contains nutrients"},{"time":45985,"text":"and there are sufficient nutrients in there"},{"time":47942,"text":"for dung beetles basically to make a living,"},{"time":50905,"text":"and so dung beetles eat dung, and their larvae"},{"time":53840,"text":"are also dung-feeders."},{"time":55995,"text":"They are grown completely in a ball of dung."},{"time":59225,"text":"Within South Africa, we've got about 800 species of dung beetles,"},{"time":63020,"text":"in Africa we've got 2,000 species of dung beetles,"},{"time":66290,"text":"and in the world we have about 6,000 species of dung beetles."},{"time":70888,"text":"So, according to dung beetles, dung is pretty good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76026,"text":"Unless you're prepared to get dung under your fingernails"},{"time":78698,"text":"and root through the dung itself, you'll never see"},{"time":81467,"text":"90 percent of the dung beetle species,"},{"time":83758,"text":"because they go directly into the dung,"},{"time":86164,"text":"straight down below it, and then they shuttle back and forth"},{"time":88776,"text":"between the dung at the soil surface"},{"time":90831,"text":"and a nest they make underground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93771,"text":"So the question is, how do they deal with this material?"},{"time":99016,"text":"And most dung beetles actually wrap it into a package of some sort."},{"time":102996,"text":"Ten percent of the species actually make a ball,"},{"time":106676,"text":"and this ball they roll away from the dung source,"},{"time":110838,"text":"usually bury it at a remote place away from the dung source,"},{"time":114274,"text":"and they have a very particular behavior"},{"time":117579,"text":"by which they are able to roll their balls."},{"time":122554,"text":"So this is a very proud owner of a beautiful dung ball."},{"time":126147,"text":"You can see it's a male"},{"time":127382,"text":"because he's got a little hair on the back of his legs there,"},{"time":129623,"text":"and he's clearly very pleased about what he's sitting on there."},{"time":134692,"text":"And then he's about to become a victim"},{"time":136604,"text":"of a vicious smash-and-grab. (Laughter)"},{"time":141853,"text":"And this is a clear indication"},{"time":144551,"text":"that this is a valuable resource."},{"time":147162,"text":"And so valuable resources have to be looked after"},{"time":151287,"text":"and guarded in a particular way, and we think"},{"time":154606,"text":"the reason they roll the balls away is because of this,"},{"time":157908,"text":"because of the competition that is involved"},{"time":160318,"text":"in getting hold of that dung."},{"time":162193,"text":"So this dung pat was actually -- well, it was a dung pat"},{"time":165390,"text":"15 minutes before this photograph was taken,"},{"time":167836,"text":"and we think it's the intense competition"},{"time":170885,"text":"that makes the beetles so well-adapted"},{"time":174765,"text":"to rolling balls of dung."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177454,"text":"So what you've got to imagine here is this animal here"},{"time":179487,"text":"moving across the African veld."},{"time":183090,"text":"Its head is down. It's walking backwards."},{"time":186438,"text":"It's the most bizarre way to actually transport your food in any particular direction,"},{"time":191809,"text":"and at the same time it's got to deal with the heat."},{"time":194675,"text":"This is Africa. It's hot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196663,"text":"So what I want to share with you now"},{"time":198370,"text":"are some of the experiments that myself and my colleagues"},{"time":201545,"text":"have used to investigate how dung beetles"},{"time":206386,"text":"deal with these problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208438,"text":"So watch this beetle,"},{"time":210975,"text":"and there's two things that I would like you to be aware of."},{"time":215119,"text":"The first is how it deals with this obstacle"},{"time":217681,"text":"that we've put in its way. See, look, it does a little dance,"},{"time":220569,"text":"and then it carries on in exactly the same direction"},{"time":223503,"text":"that it took in the first place."},{"time":227193,"text":"A little dance, and then heads off in a particular direction."},{"time":230959,"text":"So clearly this animal knows where it's going"},{"time":234336,"text":"and it knows where it wants to go,"},{"time":235675,"text":"and that's a very, very important thing,"},{"time":237560,"text":"because if you think about it, you're at the dung pile,"},{"time":239975,"text":"you've got this great big pie that you want to get away from everybody else,"},{"time":244498,"text":"and the quickest way to do it is in a straight line."},{"time":247391,"text":"So we gave them some more tasks to deal with,"},{"time":251770,"text":"and what we did here is we turned the world"},{"time":255930,"text":"under their feet. And watch its response."},{"time":265287,"text":"So this animal has actually had the whole world"},{"time":268083,"text":"turned under its feet. It's turned by 90 degrees."},{"time":270930,"text":"But it doesn't flinch. It knows exactly where it wants to go,"},{"time":273402,"text":"and it heads off in that particular direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276370,"text":"So our next question then was,"},{"time":278562,"text":"how are they doing this?"},{"time":280522,"text":"What are they doing? And there was a cue that was available to us."},{"time":283971,"text":"It was that every now and then they'd climb on top of the ball"},{"time":287098,"text":"and they'd take a look at the world around them."},{"time":289730,"text":"And what do you think they could be looking at"},{"time":291450,"text":"as they climb on top of the ball?"},{"time":293126,"text":"What are the obvious cues that this animal could use"},{"time":296681,"text":"to direct its movement? And the most obvious one"},{"time":300859,"text":"is to look at the sky, and so we thought,"},{"time":305078,"text":"now what could they be looking at in the sky?"},{"time":307342,"text":"And the obvious thing to look at is the sun."},{"time":311451,"text":"So a classic experiment here,"},{"time":314405,"text":"in that what we did was we moved the sun."},{"time":317944,"text":"What we're going to do now is shade the sun with a board"},{"time":320685,"text":"and then move the sun with a mirror"},{"time":322655,"text":"to a completely different position."},{"time":324521,"text":"And look at what the beetle does."},{"time":326433,"text":"It does a little double dance,"},{"time":329264,"text":"and then it heads back in exactly the same direction"},{"time":331543,"text":"it went in the first place."},{"time":333952,"text":"What happens now? So clearly they're looking at the sun."},{"time":337679,"text":"The sun is a very important cue in the sky for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340941,"text":"The thing is the sun is not always available to you,"},{"time":343566,"text":"because at sunset it disappears below the horizon."},{"time":347982,"text":"What is happening in the sky here"},{"time":350566,"text":"is that there's a great big pattern of polarized light in the sky"},{"time":354225,"text":"that you and I can't see. It's the way our eyes are built."},{"time":357976,"text":"But the sun is at the horizon over here"},{"time":361679,"text":"and we know that when the sun is at the horizon,"},{"time":364646,"text":"say it's over on this side,"},{"time":366190,"text":"there is a north-south, a huge pathway across the sky"},{"time":370775,"text":"of polarized light that we can't see"},{"time":373248,"text":"that the beetles can see."},{"time":376046,"text":"So how do we test that? Well, that's easy."},{"time":378905,"text":"What we do is we get a great big polarization filter,"},{"time":381847,"text":"pop the beetle underneath it, and the filter is at right angles"},{"time":386271,"text":"to the polarization pattern of the sky."},{"time":388921,"text":"The beetle comes out from underneath the filter"},{"time":393091,"text":"and it does a right-hand turn,"},{"time":395594,"text":"because it comes back under the sky"},{"time":397788,"text":"that it was originally orientated to"},{"time":400607,"text":"and then reorientates itself back"},{"time":402952,"text":"to the direction it was originally going in."},{"time":406874,"text":"So obviously beetles can see polarized light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412691,"text":"Okay, so what we've got so far is,"},{"time":415448,"text":"what are beetles doing? They're rolling balls."},{"time":418224,"text":"How are they doing it? Well, they're rolling them in a straight line."},{"time":421239,"text":"How are they maintaining it in a particular straight line?"},{"time":424817,"text":"Well, they're looking at celestial cues in the sky,"},{"time":427512,"text":"some of which you and I can't see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429756,"text":"But how do they pick up those celestial cues?"},{"time":431440,"text":"That was what was of interest to us next."},{"time":434484,"text":"And it was this particular little behavior, the dance,"},{"time":437672,"text":"that we thought was important, because look,"},{"time":440591,"text":"it takes a pause every now and then,"},{"time":442147,"text":"and then heads off in the direction that it wants to go in."},{"time":446626,"text":"So what are they doing when they do this dance?"},{"time":450863,"text":"How far can we push them before they will reorientate themselves?"},{"time":455205,"text":"And in this experiment here, what we did was we forced them"},{"time":458701,"text":"into a channel, and you can see he wasn't"},{"time":461363,"text":"particularly forced into this particular channel,"},{"time":464101,"text":"and we gradually displaced the beetle by 180 degrees"},{"time":469399,"text":"until this individual ends up going in exactly the opposite direction"},{"time":473135,"text":"that it wanted to go in, in the first place."},{"time":475700,"text":"And let's see what his reaction is"},{"time":478501,"text":"as he's headed through 90 degrees here,"},{"time":481111,"text":"and now he's going to -- when he ends up down here,"},{"time":483215,"text":"he's going to be 180 degrees in the wrong direction."},{"time":486262,"text":"And see what his response is."},{"time":488560,"text":"He does a little dance, he turns around,"},{"time":491753,"text":"and heads back in this. He knows exactly where he's going."},{"time":495487,"text":"He knows exactly what the problem is,"},{"time":497766,"text":"and he knows exactly how to deal with it,"},{"time":499361,"text":"and the dance is this transition behavior"},{"time":502062,"text":"that allows them to reorientate themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504871,"text":"So that's the dance, but after spending many years"},{"time":509663,"text":"sitting in the African bush watching dung beetles on nice hot days,"},{"time":513319,"text":"we noticed that there was another behavior"},{"time":515670,"text":"associated with the dance behavior."},{"time":518159,"text":"Every now and then, when they climb on top of the ball,"},{"time":522097,"text":"they wipe their face."},{"time":525503,"text":"And you see him do it again."},{"time":528466,"text":"Now we thought, now what could be going on here?"},{"time":531447,"text":"Clearly the ground is very hot, and when the ground is hot,"},{"time":534351,"text":"they dance more often, and when they do this particular dance,"},{"time":537086,"text":"they wipe the bottom of their face."},{"time":539056,"text":"And we thought that it could be a thermoregulatory behavior."},{"time":541755,"text":"We thought that maybe what they're doing is trying to"},{"time":543765,"text":"get off the hot soil and also spitting onto their face"},{"time":547206,"text":"to cool their head down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":549622,"text":"So what we did was design a couple of arenas."},{"time":554064,"text":"one was hot, one was cold."},{"time":556163,"text":"We shaded this one. We left that one hot."},{"time":558540,"text":"And then what we did was we filmed them with a thermal camera."},{"time":562007,"text":"So what you're looking at here is a heat image"},{"time":566423,"text":"of the system, and what you can see here emerging"},{"time":570344,"text":"from the poo is a cool dung ball."},{"time":573953,"text":"So the truth is, if you look at the temperature over here,"},{"time":577232,"text":"dung is cool. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":582212,"text":"So all we're interested in here is comparing the temperature"},{"time":585430,"text":"of the beetle against the background."},{"time":588070,"text":"So the background here is around about 50 degrees centigrade."},{"time":592014,"text":"The beetle itself and the ball are probably around about"},{"time":594622,"text":"30 to 35 degrees centigrade,"},{"time":596693,"text":"so this is a great big ball of ice cream"},{"time":599359,"text":"that this beetle is now transporting across the hot veld."},{"time":602486,"text":"It isn't climbing. It isn't dancing, because"},{"time":605189,"text":"its body temperature is actually relatively low."},{"time":608030,"text":"It's about the same as yours and mine."},{"time":611103,"text":"And what's of interest here is that little brain is quite cool."},{"time":616067,"text":"But if we contrast now what happens in a hot environment,"},{"time":620374,"text":"look at the temperature of the soil."},{"time":622524,"text":"It's up around 55 to 60 degrees centigrade."},{"time":625974,"text":"Watch how often the beetle dances."},{"time":629416,"text":"And look at its front legs. They're roaringly hot."},{"time":633958,"text":"So the ball leaves a little thermal shadow,"},{"time":636881,"text":"and the beetle climbs on top of the ball"},{"time":638815,"text":"and wipes its face, and all the time it's trying to cool itself down,"},{"time":643454,"text":"we think, and avoid the hot sand that it's walking across."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649124,"text":"And what we did then was put little boots on these legs,"},{"time":653056,"text":"because this was a way to test if the legs"},{"time":656018,"text":"were involved in sensing the temperature of the soil."},{"time":659776,"text":"And if you look over here, with boots they climb onto the ball"},{"time":663753,"text":"far less often when they had no boots on."},{"time":667944,"text":"So we described these as cool boots."},{"time":670271,"text":"It was a dental compound that we used to make these boots."},{"time":673193,"text":"And we also cooled down the dung ball, so we were able"},{"time":676080,"text":"to put the ball in the fridge, gave them a nice cool dung ball,"},{"time":679729,"text":"and they climbed onto that ball far less often"},{"time":682280,"text":"than when they had a hot ball."},{"time":683816,"text":"So this is called stilting. It's a thermal behavior"},{"time":686790,"text":"that you and I do if we cross the beach,"},{"time":688698,"text":"we jump onto a towel, somebody has this towel --"},{"time":691416,"text":"\"Sorry, I've jumped onto your towel.\" --"},{"time":692639,"text":"and then you scuttle across onto somebody else's towel,"},{"time":695203,"text":"and that way you don't burn your feet."},{"time":697408,"text":"And that's exactly what the beetles are doing here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700209,"text":"However, there's one more story I'd like to share with you,"},{"time":703424,"text":"and that's this particular species."},{"time":704996,"text":"It's from a genus called Pachysoma."},{"time":707789,"text":"There are 13 species in the genus, and they have"},{"time":710821,"text":"a particular behavior that I think you will find interesting."},{"time":716959,"text":"This is a dung beetle. Watch what he's doing."},{"time":721619,"text":"Can you spot the difference?"},{"time":724309,"text":"They don't normally go this slowly. It's in slow motion."},{"time":727541,"text":"but it's walking forwards,"},{"time":729335,"text":"and it's actually taking a pellet of dry dung with it."},{"time":732896,"text":"This is a different species in the same genus"},{"time":735350,"text":"but exactly the same foraging behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739222,"text":"There's one more interesting aspect of this"},{"time":742013,"text":"dung beetle's behavior that we found quite fascinating,"},{"time":746316,"text":"and that's that it forages and provisions a nest."},{"time":750822,"text":"So watch this individual here, and what he's trying to do"},{"time":753513,"text":"is set up a nest."},{"time":756233,"text":"And he doesn't like this first position,"},{"time":757942,"text":"but he comes up with a second position,"},{"time":759565,"text":"and about 50 minutes later, that nest is finished,"},{"time":763422,"text":"and he heads off to forage and provision"},{"time":767149,"text":"at a pile of dry dung pellets."},{"time":769503,"text":"And what I want you to notice is the outward path"},{"time":772669,"text":"compared to the homeward path, and compare the two."},{"time":777278,"text":"And by and large, you'll see that the homeward path"},{"time":779938,"text":"is far more direct than the outward path."},{"time":782769,"text":"On the outward path, he's always on the lookout"},{"time":785584,"text":"for a new blob of dung."},{"time":788049,"text":"On the way home, he knows where home is,"},{"time":789600,"text":"and he wants to go straight to it."},{"time":792818,"text":"The important thing here is that this is not a one-way trip,"},{"time":796393,"text":"as in most dung beetles. The trip here is repeated"},{"time":799783,"text":"back and forth between a provisioning site and a nest site."},{"time":804088,"text":"And watch, you're going to see"},{"time":805030,"text":"another South African crime taking place right now. (Laughter)"},{"time":809040,"text":"And his neighbor steals one of his dung pellets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813654,"text":"So what we're looking at here"},{"time":816791,"text":"is a behavior called path integration."},{"time":820119,"text":"And what's taking place is that the beetle"},{"time":822736,"text":"has got a home spot, it goes out on a convoluted path"},{"time":827039,"text":"looking for food, and then when it finds food,"},{"time":830130,"text":"it heads straight home. It knows exactly where its home is."},{"time":834438,"text":"Now there's two ways it could be doing that,"},{"time":837463,"text":"and we can test that by displacing the beetle"},{"time":840423,"text":"to a new position when it's at the foraging site."},{"time":843120,"text":"If it's using landmarks, it will find its home."},{"time":846414,"text":"If it is using something called path integration,"},{"time":849829,"text":"it will not find its home. It will arrive at the wrong spot,"},{"time":853613,"text":"and what it's doing here if it's using path integration"},{"time":856037,"text":"is it's counting its steps or measuring the distance out in this direction."},{"time":859908,"text":"It knows the bearing home, and it knows it should be in that direction."},{"time":863605,"text":"If you displace it, it ends up in the wrong place."},{"time":866733,"text":"So let's see what happens when we put this beetle"},{"time":869310,"text":"to the test with a similar experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872626,"text":"So here's our cunning experimenter."},{"time":877012,"text":"He displaces the beetle,"},{"time":879413,"text":"and now we have to see what is going to take place."},{"time":884262,"text":"What we've got is a burrow. That's where the forage was."},{"time":887356,"text":"The forage has been displaced to a new position."},{"time":890303,"text":"If he's using landmark orientation,"},{"time":892662,"text":"he should be able to find the burrow,"},{"time":894422,"text":"because he'll be able to recognize the landmarks around it."},{"time":897145,"text":"If he's using path integration,"},{"time":900188,"text":"then it should end up in the wrong spot over here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903912,"text":"So let's watch what happens"},{"time":906222,"text":"when we put the beetle through the whole test."},{"time":909513,"text":"So there he is there."},{"time":911509,"text":"He's about to head home, and look what happens."},{"time":917769,"text":"Shame."},{"time":920262,"text":"It hasn't a clue."},{"time":922496,"text":"It starts to search for its house in the right distance"},{"time":925416,"text":"away from the food, but it is clearly completely lost."},{"time":931391,"text":"So we know now that this animal uses path integration"},{"time":935609,"text":"to find its way around, and the callous experimenter"},{"time":939688,"text":"leads it top left and leaves it. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942809,"text":"So what we're looking at here are a group of animals"},{"time":946864,"text":"that use a compass, and they use the sun as a compass"},{"time":948943,"text":"to find their way around,"},{"time":950583,"text":"and they have some sort of system"},{"time":953108,"text":"for measuring that distance,"},{"time":955071,"text":"and we know that these species here actually"},{"time":958408,"text":"count the steps. That's what they use as an odometer,"},{"time":961089,"text":"a step-counting system, to find their way back home."},{"time":966226,"text":"We don't know yet what dung beetles use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":969049,"text":"So what have we learned from these animals"},{"time":971328,"text":"with a brain that's the size of a grain of rice?"},{"time":974329,"text":"Well, we know that they can roll balls in a straight line"},{"time":978440,"text":"using celestial cues."},{"time":980585,"text":"We know that the dance behavior is an orientation behavior"},{"time":983713,"text":"and it's also a thermoregulation behavior,"},{"time":986127,"text":"and we also know that they use a path integration system"},{"time":990325,"text":"for finding their way home."},{"time":992414,"text":"So for a small animal dealing with a fairly revolting substance"},{"time":996584,"text":"we can actually learn an awful lot from these things"},{"time":999353,"text":"doing behaviors that you and I couldn't possibly do."},{"time":1002985,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}